1. What was the first lesson the two boys learned?
Lesson 1: “The rich don’t work for money.” ,  reference : Begin of the lesson : “Lesson #1: The Rich Don’t Work for Money” , Chapter 1 ( pt.20)
Correct : Make quick decision 
2. How does Robert (the author) feel about dusting off the canned goods? Provide reference
incredibly boring, almost painfully so. . Reference : “We spent three hours… brushing each can… It was excruciatingly boring work.” ( pt.29) 
3. How does Robert feel about his wage? Provide reference
disappointing . Reference : "I felt like it wasn’t enough. It seemed like nothing. I was disappointed" (pt.38)
4. How did Robert’s opinion of Mike’s dad change? (not what made it change)
It became better 
5. According to Mike’s dad, what do people do when life pushed them around?
He says about 2 groups that peoples usually fall into :
1.Some let life push them around.
2.Others get angry and push back—but at the wrong things.
Reference : "People do two things. Some just let life push them around. Others get angry ... their husband or wife…" (pt.33)
6. According to Mike’s dad, what stopped scared people from taking chances?
The Fear. Especially the fear of losing, fear of not having enough money, fear of not paying the bills, etc.(pt.37)
Correct : The fear of exciment losing 
